methods.name: values
methods.description: Returns an array containing the constants of this enum class, in the order they are declared.

methods.name: valueOf
exceptions: IllegalArgumentException - if this enum class has no constant with the specified name
methods.description: Returns the enum constant of this class with the specified name. The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an enum constant in this class. (Extraneous whitespace characters are not permitted.)

enum_constants.name: AND
enum_constants.description: Checked third, these predicates must all pass along with the original predicate

enum_constants.name: OR
enum_constants.description: Checked second, only one of these predicates must pass along with the original predicate

enum_constants.name: REPLACE
enum_constants.description: Checked first, the last mod to replace the predicate wipes out all other predicates. Listen with a low EventPriority if you need to do this.
